In the `System.setProperty` line of code, you are supposed to set the path of `chromedriver.exe` file. It appears that the path you have provided(`chrome.exe`) is for browser instead of browser driver.

**Correct:**
````
System.setProperty(&quot;webdriver.chrome.driver&quot;, &quot;C:\\Users\\&lt;username&gt;\\Downloads\\chromedriver_win64\\chromedriver.exe&quot;);
````
**Inocrrect:**
````
System.setProperty(&quot;webdriver.chrome.driver&quot;,&quot;C:/Users/PrasadB/Downloads/chrome-win64/chrome-win64/chrome.exe&quot;);
````

Having said the above, since you are using selenium `v4.11.0`, setting the `chromedriver.exe` path is not mandatory any more. Which means selenium will download and manage the driver for you. All you have to do is, remove the `System.setProperty` line from your code(see below).

````
//System.setProperty(&quot;webdriver.chrome.driver&quot;,&quot;C:/Users/PrasadB/Downloads/chrome-win64/chrome-win64/chrome.exe&quot;);
WebDriver driver = new ChromeDriver();
````

